description: This '68 AMX was prepared by and raced in the 2016 Peking-Paris rally by Jim Valentine in England. The car is equipped with a full roll cage for safety reasons and improved rigidity and a full camping setup consisting of mats, tents and -20Â°C rated sleeping bags. Also included is standard rally gear, such as twin displays with GPS info and a hard-wired intercom system for communication between driver and co-driver. It even has an aux-in function for listening to music in the two headsets. Also, the car can be loaded with 200 liters of fuel. The 390 V8 is detuned to 272 horespower to run on any fuel available.
